&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;W&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;ell being.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;M&lt;/span&gt;alaise&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;a general feeling of discomfort, illness, or unease whose exact cause is difficult to identify.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Malaise is a general feeling of discomfort, illness, or lack of well-being.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anxiety&lt;/strong&gt; is a feeling of fear, dread, and uneasiness.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unease&lt;/strong&gt; is similar to&amp;nbsp;anxiety or discontent. It also explains one is&amp;nbsp;not comfortable in manner or situation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sickness&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;the state of being ill or&amp;nbsp;the feeling or fact of being affected with nausea or vomiting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;sporadic&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means occurring at irregular intervals or only in a few places; scattered or isolated. (अनियमित)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; sporadic&lt;/strong&gt; rainfall has made it difficult to predict the weather.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Irregular&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to something that does not happen at regular times; not consistent or even in pattern or occurrence. (अनियमित)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; irregular&lt;/strong&gt; attendance of the students was noted by the teacher.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the meaning of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;sporadic&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is closest to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;irregular&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scattered &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;बिखरा हुआ&lt;/span&gt;): Spread or thrown over a wide area.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The scattered papers on the desk indicated a busy workday.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frequent &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अक्सर&lt;/span&gt;): Occurring or done many times at short intervals.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She is a frequent visitor to the library.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Irksome&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;कष्टप्रद&lt;/span&gt;): Annoying or irritating.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His irksome behavior was starting to get on everyone&amp;#39;s nerves.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Truant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;us&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;explore&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the given&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;options&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
